UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304387886900805
AB  - This paper presents a computable general equilibrium model for South Korea. It is a dynamic input-output model solved by assuming equal sectoral growth rates. Its solution gives output and price relatives which measure the structural ‘distance’ of the economy from the ‘turnpike’. Comparisons of these model solutions with actual output proportions and relative prices provide insights into the South Korean industrialization process. However, the model's strict assumptions limit its applicability and provide problems of interpretation, especially in open economies.
